(18, '2014-12-31', 2, 2, 2, 1, 'I am huge fan of this restaurant until recently...I have been a frequent customer here since I LOVE their kimchi. Last week I ordered the seafood tofu (the dish I always get) and was anxiously waiting for my food. When it arrived, the broth was tasteless and the seafood consisted of 1 shrimp, 1 mussel, and a chopped piece of cuttlefish tentacle for the price of $13.95. As usual, they would come ask how our food were. For the first time, I brought up my concern regarding the tofu I ordered. I explained that the dish tasted different from before since there is no flavour to it. The waiter politely addressed my concern and brought it back in the kitchen. When the dish came back, it was really salty to the point I cannot finish it. They came back and I told them it was too salty. When it was time to leave, the waiter came again and asked me if I wanted to pack it and I said no. They did not make an effort to show that they are sorry and instead said oh maybe you do not like the korean tofu dish. They charged me in full for the dish even though I took only a few bites. Because of this, I will never return again since they never offered to cancel the dish or ask if I wanted another item (not like I would have accepted it but it would have been a nice gesture).....very disappointed :(', 3),

